  "text": "Above mentioned facts and an observation that many optimization problems which are hard to solve on general graphs are easy on trees makes the detection tree structures in a graph a very promising task. A powerful tool of algorithmic graph theory like tree decomposition [CITATION_1] can help detect trees and obtain the treewidth, a measure of the \"tree-likeness\" of the graph.",
